# ChaCha20-Poly1305 RFC 8439 test-vector spec
#
# Exercises src/os/crypto/chacha20_poly1305.spl against canonical RFC 8439
# known-answer test vectors. Pure-Simple, no vendor deps, no externs.
#
# Purpose: load-validated reference baseline for the scalar implementation.
# A future SIMD optimisation or fix to the Poly1305 tag bug can be verified
# against these vectors once the test runner gains compiled-mode execution.
#
# Execution note: the unit test runner (interpreter mode) verifies file
# loading and syntax, but does NOT execute it-block bodies. Assertions here
# are structurally correct and use the real function signatures; they will
# become live regression gates when the runner executes in compiled mode.
#
# Known Poly1305 tag bug for 114-byte inputs:
#   doc/01_research/local/chacha_poly_tag_bug_2026-04-17.md
#
# §2.8.2 ciphertext bytes: confirmed correct (impl passes ciphertext check).
# §2.8.2 tag bytes:        known-diverging (impl bug per above doc).

use std.spipe.*
use os.crypto.chacha20_poly1305.{chacha20_poly1305_encrypt, chacha20_poly1305_decrypt, Chacha20Poly1305Result}

